Obs 4:    0.056  0.000  0.000  0.000  0.842 

🚀 2. TRANSITION MODEL (B matrices) - PyMDP obj_array format
======================================================================
Matrix shape: (16, 16, 4)
Interpretation: P(next_state | current_state, action)
Dimensions: [next_state, current_state, action]
Each B[:,:,action] matrix should have columns summing to 1.0

Up Action (B[:,:,0]):
  Sample column sums (should be 1.0): [1. 1. 1. 1. 1.]

Down Action (B[:,:,1]):
  Sample column sums (should be 1.0): [1. 1. 1. 1. 1.]

Left Action (B[:,:,2]):
  Sample column sums (should be 1.0): [1. 1. 1. 1. 1.]

Right Action (B[:,:,3]):
  Sample column sums (should be 1.0): [1. 1. 1. 1. 1.]

💎 3. PREFERENCES (C vector) - PyMDP obj_array format
======================================================================
Vector shape: (16,)
Interpretation: log P(observation preferred)
Higher values = more preferred observations

Key position preferences:
  Goal (3, 3): 5.000
  Obstacle (1, 1): -2.000
  Obstacle (2, 2): -2.000
  Range: [-2.000, 5.000]

🎲 4. PRIOR BELIEFS (D vector) - PyMDP obj_array format
